<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.293307>
    bibo:endPage "51" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:startPage "43" ;
    bibo:volume "2429" ;
    dc:creator "Kajihara, Hiroshi; Lindsay, Dhugal J." ;
    dc:date "2010" ;
    dc:title "Dinonemertes shinkaii sp. nov., (Nemertea: Hoplonemertea: Polystilifera: Pelagica) a new species of bathypelagic nemertean" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.293308>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.293309>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.293310>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.294256>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.293312> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.293308>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Dinonemertes shinkaii sp. nov., holotype, JAMSTEC 6 K 549 SS 4. A. Living specimen taken in situ by a video camera on the manned submersible Shinkai 6500 at a depth of 2343 m; head to the right. B. Living specimen taken on board the R. V. Yokosuka showing the general shape and the coloration, ventral view; head to the right. C. Head of the living specimen, dorsal view. D. Preserved specimen, dorsal view; head to the right." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/293308/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.293309>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Dinonemertes shinkaii sp. nov., holotype, JAMSTEC 6 K 549 SS 4, transverse sections. A. Body wall in the anterior intestinal region, showing the rudimentary development of the body-wall musculature on the lateral sides (arrowhead); the epidermis is largely exfoliated. B. Rhynchodaeum surrounded by circular muscles (arrowhead). C. Dorsal surface in the posterior region of the body to show the appearance of the epidermis. D. Rhynchocoel wall comprised of outer circular, middle longitudinal, and inner circular muscle layers; pseudostriated muscle fibre in the outer circular layer is indicated by an arrowhead. E. Pseudostriated muscle fibre in the rhynchocoel inner circular muscle layer." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/293309/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.293310>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Dinonemertes shinkaii sp. nov., holotype, JAMSTEC 6 K 549 SS 4, transverse sections. A. Proboscis anterior chamber with everted (exterior) and inverted (interior) states; the 24 nerves in the everted proboscis are indicated by arrowheads. B. Proboscis anterior chamber in inverted state; arrowhead shows a “ ganglion ” between the proboscis nerves. C. Anterior portion of the proboscis posterior chamber; arrowheads indicating the proboscis nerves. D. Posterior portion of the proboscis posterior chamber; arrowheads indicate the incomplete nerve layer." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/293310/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.294256>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Dinonemertes shinkaii sp. nov., holotype, JAMSTEC 6 K 549 SS 4, transverse sections. A. Brain region, showing dorsal cephalic vascular anastomosis (arrowhead). B. Pylorus opening to the dorsal wall of the intestinal caecum. C. Intestinal lateral diverticulum. D. Caudal vessel above anal opening." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/294256/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.293312>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Dinonemertes shinkaii sp. nov., holotype, JAMSTEC 6 K 549 SS 4, transverse sections. A. Vascular plug in the stomach region. B. Mid-dorsal vessel and a pair of lateral vessels before merging posteriorly to form a caudal vessel above the intestine. C. Caudal vessel; the two lateral nerves are about to merge above the intestine. D. Oocytes linearly arrayed in the ovary; nurse cells surrounding the oocytes." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/293312/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

